TvAd
TV Advertising
The premier way of advertising. Very broad reach, but not very targeted. Up to 25% effectiveness, but very expensive. However, the combination of audio and video on your advertising cannot be underestimated.
~
RaAd
Radio Advertising
The impactful way to reach people on the road. Up to 20% effectiveness, it is slightly more targeted than TV, and cheaper to promote. Goes great as a subtle reminder to the more aggressive TV campaigns.
~
NeAd
Newspaper Advertising
Everyone reads the papers! Moderately targeted advertising can account for up to 15% effectiveness. Costs are very affordable. Due to the disposable nature of newspapers, however, constant upkeeping is needed for it to be effective.
~
MaAd
Magazine Advertising
The most targeted of all ads. Can account for up to 10% effectiveness, and more expensive than newspapers. However, magazines are read several times, so your exposure is higher than that of newspapers.
~
